    "index:LeftRight-0:heading": {
      "original": " Keep what you need. Delete the rest. ",
      "value": null,
      "pages": {
        "index.html": 1
      },
      "total": 1
    },
    "index:LeftRight-0:text_content": {
      "original": "<p>This starter aims to get developers building their own site quickly in CloudCannon. It strikes a balance between minimal boilerplate and useful features out of the box:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Tailwind CSS v4</li>\n<li>Blog with pagination &amp; tags</li>\n<li>Visual editing with Editable Regions</li>\n<li>Header and Footer controls</li>\n<li>Create and delete pages</li>\n<li>SEO controls</li>\n</ul>\n",
      "value": null,
      "pages": {
        "index.html": 1
      },
      "total": 1
    },
    "index:LeftRight-1:button_text": {
      "original": " CloudCannon Docs ",
      "value": null,
      "pages": {
        "index.html": 1
      },
      "total": 1
    },
    "index:LeftRight-1:heading": {
      "original": " You choose your editing experience. ",
      "value": null,
      "pages": {
        "index.html": 1
      },
      "total": 1
    },
    "index:LeftRight-1:text_content": {
      "original": "<p>A flexible git-backed CMS that specialises in editing markdown and data files.</p>\n<p>Visual editing allows you to preview your changes live before you save them.</p>\n<p>Git-backed means you can keep all your familiar git workflows, while providing an easy-to-understand interface for non-technical editors to collaborate via git.</p>\n",
      "value": null,
      "pages": {
        "index.html": 1
      },
      "total": 1
    },
    "index:hero:button_text": {
      "original": " Get Started ",
      "value": null,
      "pages": {
        "index.html": 1
      },
      "total": 1
    },
    "index:hero:heading": {
      "original": " Astro Minimal Starter ",
      "value": null,
      "pages": {
        "index.html": 1
      },
      "total": 1
    },
    "index:hero:subheading": {
      "original": "<p>A <strong>minimal</strong> starting point for developers looking to build a website with Astro, using Editable Regions in CloudCannon. Create your own copy, and start creating your own components to use in the Visual Editor.</p>\n<p>Once you've explored this minimal starter, consider  taking a look at the <a href=\"https://github.com/CloudCannon/astro-component-starter\">Astro Component Starter</a> to assist in building out your components.</p>\n",
      "value": null,
      "pages": {
        "index.html": 1
      },
      "total": 1
    },
